Asciidoc FX is a book / document editor to build HTML, PDF, Epub or Mobi ebooks.

.AsciidocFX
image::images/asciidocfx.png[]

== Features

* Real-Time Preview
* Multi-platform (Windows, Mac, Linux ..)
* Creating Asciidoc Books
* Creating Markdown Books
* Creating PDF, HTML, Epub, Mobi, Docbook
* Epub Viewer
* External Browser Support
* Table Generator
* MathJax Extension
* PlantUML Extension
* Filesystem Tree Extension

== How to Install AsciidocFX

You can download the latest release from https://github.com/asciidocfx/AsciidocFX/releases[Github releases page].

=== Installation Notes

Releases includes JRE 8 out-of-box. You don't need to install it in extra. If you have already installed JRE 8, you can download *No_JRE builds

PlantUML extension needs Graphviz, if you will use it, then install it.

You should install Microsoft Core Fonts on Linux OSes also.

==== Linux/Ubuntu/Debian

Graphviz and Microsoft core fonts dependencies:

[source,bash]
----
sudo apt-get install graphviz ttf-mscorefonts-installer
----

==== Mac OS X

Graphviz dependency:

[source,bash]
----
ruby -e "$(curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Homebrew/install/master/install)"
brew install graphviz
----

==== Windows

Graphviz dependency:

http://www.graphviz.org/pub/graphviz/stable/windows/graphviz-2.38.msi


